cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NA

The paper deals with machine learning applications and algorithms for solving two specific problems related to sparse vectors and tensor decomposition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques and analysis of algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of random linear subspaces and overcomplete 3-tensors could also place the paper in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
